\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 cup sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup water\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Put the sugar and water in a small \cf2 saucepan\cf0 . Cook over low heat, stirring, until the sugar dissolves. (Alternatively, heat in the microwave.) Store in a sealed container in the refrigerator for up to 1 month.\
Yield: about 1 1/2 cups\
